# Hybrid AI Framework (PINN-NSGA-II) for Multi-Objective Tablet Manufacturing Optimization

## Overcoming High-Load Paracetamol Limitations

---

### 📌 Project Overview

This repository contains the complete code and documentation for the research paper:

**"A Hybrid AI Framework (PINN-NSGA-II) for Multi-Objective Tablet Manufacturing Optimization: Overcoming High-Load Paracetamol Limitations"**

**Authors:** Babuker A. Abdalla & Prof. Abdelkarim Mohamed  
**Affiliation:** Postgraduate College, Nile Valley University, Atbara, Sudan  
**Contact:** babuker@protonmail.com | +249-123-638-638

---

### 🎯 Research Objective

To develop a **physics-informed hybrid AI framework** that integrates:

- **Physics-Informed Neural Network (PINN)** — embedding Heckel compaction equation and Elastic Failure Risk Function (EFRF)
- **NSGA-II** — multi-objective evolutionary optimization

The framework identifies **Pareto-optimal high-load paracetamol formulations** (≥90% API) that satisfy mechanical constraints:  
✅ Tensile Strength (σₜ) ≥ 2 MPa  
✅ EFRF < 0.5 (zero capping risk)

---

### 📊 Key Results

| Metric | Value |
|--------|-------|
| **R² (Test Set)** | 0.96 ± 0.02 |
| **RMSE** | 0.08 ± 0.01 MPa |
| **MAE** | 0.06 ± 0.01 MPa |
| **Optimal API Loading** | ~90.5% |
| **Experimental Reduction** | ~70% |

**Statistical Significance:** PINN outperformed MLP, Random Forest, and XGBoost (paired t-test, p < 0.05).

